<TEXT>
us members of the mount everest international 
peace climb returned home friday after placing 20 climbers on the 
summit of the worlds highest peak 
expedition leader jim whittaker said placing american soviet 
and chinese mountaineers side by side on the summit was a model for 
the superpowers to emulate 
we have a bond that will never stop said whittaker who in 
1963 became the first american to reach the top of everest 
my proudest moment was when we put the first group on the 
summit to have that vision become a reality was a wonderful 
moment 
the first of the 20 climbers reached the 29028foot summit on 
may 7 and were followed by the others over the next few days 
tibetans who assisted in the climb also reached the summit 
previously the record number of climbers to reach the top of 
everest with a single expedition was 17 
the climbers said they collected about two tons of garbage while 
on the mountain from previous expeditions as well as their own 
some was buried some was burned and some was carried off the 
mountain to be recycled in china said dan branley a spokesman for 
the climb 
the expedition which began in february cost more than 1 
million it was being paid for by us corporate sponsors 
including the ll bean camping gear company of freeport maine 
</TEXT>
