<TEXT>
two activists for a radical environmental 
group were arrested friday in connection with a bomb blast that 
ripped their car apart but the duo and their supporters painted 
them as victims not criminals 
the evidence is strong they were transporting this device and 
thats why they were arrested said oakland police lt mike sims 
at a friday news conference 
based on our determination of the placement of the device in 
the car we believe they should have known it was there we believe 
it went off accidently 
but in an interview from his jail cell darryl cherney who was 
arrested along with judi bari hotly denied carrying any explosive 
devices and insisted that police investigate who was trying to kill 
the pair 
we are demanding that the oakland police department 
and the fbi seek out this assassin and bring whoever it is to 
justice immediately said cherney 33 describing himself and 
bari as victims 
baris attorney susan jordan said her client also denied any 
involvement with explosives during a meeting at baris hospital 
bedsise 
bari 40 required surgery at highland hospital for a fractured 
pelvis and suffered other injuries and was in listed stable 
condition friday cherney who suffered minor injuries including a 
head cut was treated and released thursday night 
the two earth first supporters were being held for 
investigation of possession and transportation of explosives 
cherney was booked into city jail and bari was under guard at the 
hospital 
jordan said that its inconceiveable that they would destroy 
their movement by doing that its always easy to charge somebody 
whos unpopular 
jordan added if you had a bomb wouldnt you be careful 
enough not to place it where it could injure you 
the bomb exploded on an oakland street just before noon thursday 
as bari and cherney were driving to a rally at the university of 
californiasanta cruz 
the blast blew out the windows and the rear drivers side door 
of baris station wagon other doors were blown open and the roof 
was bowed upward 
i dont believe it said mark huntington a friend of the 
pair and an earth first supporter if the police produced 
evidence and put it on tv i still wouldnt believe it i think 
they planted it the fbi has a lot of reasons to get rid of 
darryl and judi 
about 30 supporters of earth first on friday maintained a vigil 
outside police department headquarters in downtown oakland vowing 
not to leave until cherney and bari were freed 
some in the crowd played guitars and held signs reading stop 
blaming the victim trees not bombs and the fbi did it 
as many as 200 supporters gathered outside the police station 
friday night wearing earth first tshirts and singing folk songs 
sims said authorities served three search warrants and found 
evidence in several places that led to the arrests thursday night 
police searched cherneys van and a berkeley house occupied by 
several members of another environmentalist group seeds of peace 
bari and cherney had visited the house wednesday night and 
cherneys van was parked outside 
the pair described by friends as dedicated pacifists were key 
figures in planning mississippi summer in the california 
redwoods an environmentalist effort to halt what they describe 
as excessive logging of oldgrowth timber in northern california 
both were in the san francisco bay area to drum up support for 
the summerlong campaign 
the effort patterned after the mississippi summer civil 
rights protests that drew thousands of college students to the 
south in 1964 has heightened tensions along the northern 
california coast where environmentalists and the logging industry 
have long been at odds 
although bari and cherneys supporters said the two activists 
are committed to nonviolent change earth first has become known 
for tactics that include sabotage and vandalism including tree 
spiking driving spikes into soontobeharvested trees to 
damage logging equipment 
daniel barron an earth first organizer from san francisco 
said about a dozen people have received anonymous death threats 
such as one that was signed committee for the death of earth 
first 
one threat included a picture of bari with the cross hairs of a 
rifle sight drawn across her face said betty ball of the mendocino 
environmental center 
but environmentalists have not been the only targets at 
louisianapacific lumber co spokesman shepard tucker said a pipe 
bomb exploded two weeks ago at a mill in cloverdale an 
investigation into that incident is continuing said the sonoma 
county sheriffs department 
</TEXT>
