<TEXT>
president bush says he will use next 
weeks summit with soviet president mikhail gorbachev to make the 
case for keeping germany in nato 
the president vacationing at his family compound at this 
oceanfront resort late friday night signed a 4 billion spending 
package that includes 720 million in emergency aid for panama and 
nicaragua 
the measure finally passed congress in the wee hours friday 
morning bush signed it at 1019 pm after an air force jet rushed 
it to pease air force base in new hampshire and it was driven to 
his home here 
the president did so despite misgivings about what the white 
house regards as porkbarrel addons by congress and concerns about 
restrictions on his ability to enter into international agreements 
affecting nato 
in a statement bush said the 720 million will help restore 
peace and support the emerging democracies in panama and 
nicaragua but he expressed regret that the congress has used 
this important legislation to enact many special interest 
provisions that are not in response to dire emergencies 
he also criticized congress for cutting 2 billion from defense 
programs to offset about half of the 4 billionplus cost of the 
spending bill 
in a presummit interview with french television bush said it 
is not his problem whether gorbachev is being hemmed in on arms 
control and troop cutbacks by the soviet high command 
i gather hes in pretty strong control now but facing 
enormous problems bush said in the interview thursday the white 
house released a transcript friday 
but its not my role to figure out whether gorbachev is having 
a problem with his right or his left its mine to deal with whats 
on the table and whats on the table is a strong soviet leader 
clearly in charge with whom we have a lot of business items he 
said 
i will approach him and make my case for a united germany in 
nato he said 
in moscow on friday gorbachev said after meeting with french 
president francois mitterrand that if the west insists on making 
germany a member of the western military alliance he would be 
forced to take a fresh look at its polities on arms control and 
european security 
the white house declined comment on gorbachevs warning 
spokesman doug davidson said 
bush hit the golf links with weekend guest transportation 
secretary sam skinner shortly after arriving friday he was 
expected to spend today jogging playing tennis boating and 
getting in another 18 holes 
bush had called the presidents of panama and nicaragua before 
leaving washington on friday to assure them help soon would be on 
its way 
the measure he signed provides 420 million for panama 
rebuilding after us economic sanctions and an invasion of 
american forces last december to topple manuel antonio noriega 
nicaraguas new government led by usbacked president violeta 
chamorro will receive 300 million 
the spending bill includes 12 billion needed to make up a 
shortfall in food stamp funds for the current fiscal year which 
ends sept 30 545 million for veterans benefits 166 million for 
head start 432 million for fighting forest fires 110 million 
for the census and 33 million for nasa 
it also includes 75 million to meet refugee needs around the 
world 45 million in antinarcotics aid to bolivia and peru 30 
million for aid to caribbean countries and 30 million for africa 
the final version dropped 10 million that the senate wanted to 
spend to build a new us embassy in lithuania 
bush complained the legislation would infringe upon my 
constitutional authority over the conduct of diplomacy by 
requiring him to give congress 30 days notice of agreements 
involving nato he said he would regard those provisions as merely 
advisory 
bush who will not return to the white house until monday had 
no special presummit briefings planned his chief of staff john 
sununu national security adviser brent scowcroft and press 
secretary marlin fitzwater did not even accompany him to maine 
in addition to skinner and his wife honey the bushes weekend 
guests included houston friends charles and sally neblett and son 
marvin bush his wife margaret and their children marshall and 
walker 
 
