<TEXT>
defense secretary dick cheney plans to shuffle 
millions of dollars among the pentagons accounts to keep as many 
as 68000 of its employees from losing their jobs 
traditionally the defense secretary would make such a move with 
the consent of key members of congress but cheney says he plans to 
go ahead with this regardless of whether all the necessary 
lawmakers agree 
we want to protect military personnel from the effects of 
shortages in the manpower accounts he said friday last fall 
congress said it expected us to pursue this kind of reprogramming 
and thats what ive been trying to do for the past five months 
the pentagon has asked for authority to move 852 million from 
other accounts to avoid the dismissal of military personnel by 
october such a shift of funds from one pocket to another is known 
in washington jargon as a reprogramming 
such shifts of money are customarily submitted to the chairmen 
and ranking minority members of the house and senate armed services 
committees and the corresponding appropriations defense 
subcommittees 
the pentagon has estimated that without the reprogramming 
authority 44100 to 68200 military personnel would have to be 
fired by oct 1 between 32000 and 36000 people would be frozen 
in their current jobs 57000 to 67000 promotions would be 
delayed and 59000 to 115900 fewer men and women could be brought 
into the armed forces 
cheney said he has the agreement of seven of the eight 
lawmakers with only rep les aspin dwis chairman of the house 
armed services committee holding out 
if no acceptable agreement can be worked out by the first week 
congress is back from its recess then i will use the authority i 
have to reprogram the necessary funds said cheney 
i have agreed to make one more good faith effort and try to 
reach a solution to which all eight chairmen and ranking members of 
the key committees can agree he said 
congress will return from recess june 5 
aspin was traveling and unavailable for comment a committee 
source speaking on condition he not be identified agreed the 
pentagon has the authority to move the funds around but said there 
has been a gentlemens agreement to consult with congress 
what cheney is doing is trying to break the gentlemens 
agreement he said 
</TEXT>
