capital of medellin has left 22 people dead and 27 injured eight 
bombs have exploded in colombia in the last two weeks killing a 
total of 34 people and injuring more than 320 
the medellin cocaine cartel has offered 4300 for every police 
officer killed so far this month 33 have been assassinated 
police said 
the army and police said they were mobilizing about 230000 
troops to ensure peaceful elections 
bogota is an armed camp military checkpoints line major streets 
and highways and armored personnel carriers mounted with machine 
guns patrol the cities soldiers are everywhere 
it is difficult to have a conversation with a colombian these 
days without the subject getting around to bombs and other 
terrorist acts 
the violence is keeping people away from public areas and 
overwhelmingly reducing their activities it might also keep people 
at home for the elections camilo castellanos a social 
scientist told the associated press 
a low voter turnout could wrest legitimacy from the winner that 
may be exactly what the perpetrators of the violence are seeking in 
their campaigns to destabilize politics officials say 
the current president virgilio barco is barred by the 
constitution from seeking a second consecutive term 
security concerns have prevented many candidates from appearing 
in public forcing them to conduct their campaigns through 
television and radio 
these are the most tense and difficult elections in colombian 
history antonio navarro the presidential candidate for the 
leftwing m19 party told reporters wednesday 
navarro took over as m19 candidate after his predecessor 
carlos pizarro was murdered in april by an assailant who shot him 
to death on a commercial jetliner over bogota it is unclear 
whether drug traffickers killed him 
the other assassinated presidential candidate was leftist 
bernardo jaramillo who was killed march 22 police said he was 
killed by the medellin cartel 
in medellin five bodies with hands and feet bound were found 
friday on a highway the police spokeswoman said the police have 
not been able to identify the victims 
a 44pound bomb exploded friday morning at an office building in 
a wealthy medellin neighborhood the spokeswoman said three people 
were hurt and nearby apartments and stores were damaged 
she said one of the three assassinated police officers was shot 
to death on her way to work friday morning 
on thursday a powerful car bomb blew up at a police post 
outside the luxury intercontinental hotel killing five people and 
injuring 22 police said three of the dead were police officers 
the police spokeswoman said unidentified attackers also stormed 
a medellin office thursday night fatally shooting three men and 
two women 
that same night four people were murdered elsewhere in the 
city she said 
military spokesman col eduardo arevalo on wednesday said the 
rebel national liberation army on tuesday kidnapped two mayors two 
mayorselect and three city councilmen in the northwestern state 
of antioquia 
the bogota daily newspaper el tiempo citing military sources 
reported this week that the national liberation army and another 
insurgent group the revolutionary armed forces of colombia are 
planning to sabotage presidential elections 
</TEXT>
