franz schoenhuber 66 said after resigning friday that a 
small clique of extremist functionaries existed at top party 
levels and that he was not responsible for recent clashes between 
police and party members 
mainstream politicians in bonn said his decision marks the 
nearcertain demise of one of europes most controversial political 
parties which went from a mushrooming political force to a fringe 
group in disarray 
otto lambsdorff head of chancellor helmut kohls junior 
coalition partners the free democrats said friday the remains 
of this party will soon scatter themselves into the wind 
the republicans main office in munich said schoenhubers former 
deputy johanna grund 56 will replace him until a new chairperson 
is elected 
schoenhuber led the republicans to headspinning fame last year 
championing xenophobic and rightwing platforms to appeal to west 
germans tired of competing with foreigners for scarce jobs and 
housing 
beginning with west berlin in january 1989 the republicans 
scored large gains in state and local elections and also won 72 
percent in last junes elections for the european parliament 
landing schoenhuber a seat there 
the party claimed its membership climbed from 18000 to 26000 
the past year 
but the wind went out of schoenhubers sails after the east 
german revolution last fall and the sudden realization that german 
reunification was no longer just a dream with every mainstream 
party embracing unification the republicans lost much of their 
nationalist appeal 
in recent state elections the republicans mustered less than 2 
percent of the vote they slipped badly in national polls far 
below the 5 percent needed to gain seats in the federal parliament 
in scheduled dec 2 elections 
in recent days schoenhuber repeatedly cautioned that the party 
was heading too far right and was becoming an extremist rightwing 
group his charges drew fire from other party leaders 
schoenhuber said friday he could not take further responsibility 
for the party following clashes between police and party members 
during recent rallies for oct 14 bavarian state parliamentary 
elections he said he himself was withdrawing as a candidate for 
parliament in those elections 
farright political parties in west germany have a history of 
fizzling out unable to sustain strong membership in a nation where 
the nazi past makes the electorate especially sensitive 
