<TEXT>
the navy and independent analysts will conduct 
new tests over the next two weeks in the hopes of determining 
exactly what caused the explosion aboard the uss iowa that claimed 
47 lives 
congress called for the testing and the navy said it would 
comply in light of congressional findings announced on friday 
that lawmakers said cast grave doubt on the navys official 
conclusion that a troubled sailor probably caused the blast a year 
ago 
officials of the general accounting office told members of the 
senate armed services committee on friday that the iowa explosion 
may well have been an accident 
the navy in a report last september concluded that gunners 
mate clayton hartwig probably set off the april 19 1989 explosion 
by inserting a chemical detonator between bags of powder 
the lawyer representing hartwigs family said the navy should 
pay them the same amount it spent on its first investigation more 
than 4 million 
they ought to give the family at least that much to compensate 
for the hell they have put them through kreig brusnahan said 
from his cleveland office 
i am more convinced than ever that we have a legitimate claim 
for intentional and negligent infliction of emotion distress 
against the navy brusnahan said 
brusnahan expects to submit a claim to the navy within 90 days 
the navy will have six months to respond if the claim is rejected 
brusnahan said he will file with the federal courts 
the navys chief of naval operations adm carlisle ah trost 
ordered on friday that vice adm peter heckman take over the 
renewed investigation heckman is director of the navys sea 
systems command which oversees the services naval weapons and 
supervises how ships are run and built 
rear adm richard milligan who supervised the first navy 
inquiry will not be involved in the new investigation and will 
instead remain at his post as a budget director in the navys 
planning and programing office 
the navy and the sandia national laboratories will cooperate on 
the new tests and the navy pledged on friday to make the findings 
of their study public 
in its report to congress the gao cited tests conducted by 
analysts at sandia that indicated that the iowa explosion may have 
been caused by the unintentionally highspeed overramming of 
gunpowder bags this meant the bags might have been rammed too hard 
and too far into the barrel of one of the ships 16inch guns 
congress sought advice from scientists at the sandia lab in 
albuquerque nm because they found fault with the navys initial 
finding that hartwig was most probably responsible for the 
killer blast 
the sandia lab had conducted tests on 8inch guns which 
indicated that when an overram occurred with the gunpowder pellets 
in the bags jumbled from their normal straightacross pattern an 
occurrence that could easily happen analysts said enough 
friction was produced to cause an explosion 
as for the navys theory that a saboteur ignited the explosion 
sandia analysts said forms of some of the chemical constituents of 
the theorized ignitor were either commonly used in the turrets or 
are part of the maritime environment 
the navy in reopening its investigation ordered a halt to any 
firing of 16inch guns aboard the services four battleships 
sen sam nunn dga chairman of the senate armed services 
committee said he expected fridays testimony would expose 
significant shortcomings in the navys investigation and would cast 
grave doubt on the conclusions and that i believe that the 
testimony we have heard has done that and more 
sen john glenn dohio who represents hartwigs home state 
said the navy blamed the seaman because of its inability to find 
other reasons thats wrong the rush to blame hartwig was flat 
wrong 
sen carl levin dmich added the navys conclusion is 
seriously undermined 
but sen john warner of virginia the ranking republican on the 
armed services committee said its far too early to jump to any 
conclusions about a firing system that has worked tens of 
thousands of times since world war ii 
defense secretary dick cheney said he would reserve judgment on 
the new reports until additional investigations are completed 
navy officials did the best job they could now theres new 
evidence new information that warrants reopening the 
investigation cheney said 
