in the clash in south lebanon lebanese security sources said 
the guerrillas ambushed a south lebanon army convoy near the town 
of shebaa in the eastern sector of the israelioccupied border zone 
israel established the 6to10miledeep zone to curb guerrilla 
raids into northern galilee when it withdrew the bulk of its army 
from south lebanon in mid1985 three years after it invaded 
the israeli military also reported four guerrillas killed and 
said members of the south lebanon army which is trained and 
supplied by israel suffered no casualties an army spokesman said 
the attackers were members of george habashs popular front for the 
liberation of palestine 
the popular front in a series of communiques issued in beirut 
acknowledged four of its fighters had died and said the attack was 
to avenge the massacre of seven palestinian workers near tel aviv 
on sunday 
the front is made up of palestinian and leftist groups which 
regularly attack the israelis and their militia allies in south 
lebanon 
lebanese security sources speaking on condition of anonymity 
said the guerrillas detonated three remotecontrol bombs on a road 
as the convoy passed 
it was the heaviest guerrilla raid in the heavily guarded buffer 
zone in several weeks 
</TEXT>
