<TEXT>
a moderate earthquake shook the 
portuguese capital for a few seconds saturday but caused no damage 
or injuries authorities said 
the quake which registered 40 on the richter scale was 
centered 90 miles west of lisbon in the atlantic ocean according 
to lisbons national institute for meteorology and geophysics 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 a quake registering 4 can cause moderate 
damage in a populated area 
much of lisbon was destroyed by a powerful earthquake and an 
ensuing tidal wave and fire in 1755 the city center was rebuilt 
and has since suffered several less serious quakes 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

