15 months and nine of them raised at least 2 million 
twentythree pacs spent more than 1 million in the study period 
three topped 2 million 
topping the fundraising list was the teamsters union pac which 
reported raising 67 million in the 15month period the teamsters 
pac also was first in spending at 46 million and in the 49 
million it had on hand as of march 31 
another labor pac that of the letter carriers union narrowly 
eclipsed the teamsters in donations to candidates with 
contributions totaling 884600 in the study period 2000 more 
than the teamsters group 
american telephone amp telegraphs pac was the leading corporate 
pac with 18 million in receipts disbursements 17 million 
and contributions to candidates 829000 
