unwanted pregnancy drug addiction and welfare 
weve built a lot of equity in our name here said sullivan 
she and other officials worry the clubs historic stature will 
be compromised and reliable donors who account for at least half 
the lowell clubs annual 250000 budget will be put off by the 
name change 
people will begin wondering what else has changed sullivan 
said 
other clubs like the nations oldest in stamford conn have 
lodged similar objections 
but bellows said the change was practical and inevitable 
nostalgia had to go by the wayside here in favor of 
survival she said in a telephone interview keeping the 
traditional name was a kind of frivolous luxury we didnt have 
the issue arose two years ago during a girls clubs lawsuit 
against the boys clubs of america inc which had decided to change 
its name to boys and girls clubs of america inc to reflect its 
growing coed membership 
the case was eventually settled out of court when the girls 
clubs agreed to accept 760000 and withdraw its objections 
but girls clubs officials still worried the public would assume 
the two organizations had merged the name change was approved by 
the national body at its annual meeting and made official in may 
the old motto it doesnt matter where a girl comes from as 
long as she knows where she is going also was changed to the 
more sobering growing up is serious business 
girls inc has hired a public relations firm and plans a 
national tv print and radio campaign this summer trumpeting its 
educational programs 
but in lowell sullivan said the clubs reputation needs no 
enhancement 
we are steeped in tradition and dont need a new identity 
said sullivan i have a problem with the assumption that a 
national group knows whats best for this community 
clubs have until 1992 to decide whether to go along with the new 
name slogan and image 
any that decides not to could become a nonvoting affiliate of 
the national organization 
either way the kids dont really care said mary kajanka 
president of the lowell clubs board of trustees all they care 
about is having some place to go and someone to care for them 
</TEXT>
