redwood summer a threemonth series of nonviolent protests 
planned for this summer 
modeling their plans after the mississippi summer civil 
rights protests of 1964 supporters hope hundreds of protesters 
will flock to northern california forests to participate in 
blockades and sitins against logging 
we fully expected this oppression to come down if we were 
effective cherney said 
friends describe bari and cherney as committed to nonviolence 
and folksinger utah phillips credits bari with helping unite 
