clearcutting of oldgrowth forests 
bari also led a recently successful drive to renounce 
treespiking in northern california a labor organizer bari saw 
the controversial practice as an attack on the working class 
phillips said the campaign came after a mill worker was seriously 
injured three years ago while cutting a spiked tree 
earth first was founded in 1979 with the slogan no compromise 
in defense of mother earth 
the group is loosely organized with no officers board of 
directors or formal members supporters refer instead to the 
movement the decentralized structure makes it impossible to 
estimate membership but more than 10000 people subscribe to the 
earth first journal which is published eight times a year 
earth first cofounder david foreman 43 says the group is 
dedicated to defending the earth at all costs in 1985 he wrote 
ecodefense a field guide to monkeywrench which includes 
instructions on how to down power lines and spike trees 
foreman and three others were arrested in may 1989 and later 
indicted on charges of conspiring to sabotage nuclear power and 
arms plants in arizona california and colorado their trial 
originally scheduled for april has been postponed until september 
an anonymous telephone caller who said he represented earth 
first claimed responsibility for attacks on the california 
cattlemens association headquarters in sacramento and a livestock 
auction warehouse in dixon in the same january day in 1989 said 
ross 
in april thousands of people in the santa cruz area were 
without electricity for hours after two utility towers were the 
targets of sabotage believed to be the work of a splinter group of 
earth first called earth night action group according to police 
earth first supporters planned to maintain a 24hour vigil at 
oakland police headquarters until cherney and bari are released 
this only deepens our commitment to nonviolence and i hope 
it does the same for everybody cherney said 
