a tropical depression spawning rains that could 
help ease south floridas drought dissolved saturday as it passed 
over the florida straits 
the system still threatened to dump heavy rains over south 
florida but the center dissolved saturday morning 
water officials feared the rain may not travel as far north as 
lake okeechobee the backup water supply for most southern florida 
cities 
the system kicked up high seas and made weekend boating 
hazardous 
the depressions center moved through the florida keys in a 
slow erratic path to the northeast as it dissolved into a 
rainstorm forecasters said 
a depression is officially classified as a tropical storm and is 
given a name if its top sustained surface winds reach 39 mph those 
that reach 74 mph are classified as hurricanes 
the atlantic hurricane season runs from june 1 to nov 30 
