tens of thousands of flagwaving 
whites staged the largest proapartheid rally since president fw 
de klerk came to power last year and cheered a pledge by rightwing 
leaders to defend white power 
andries treurnicht leader of the main opposition conservative 
party said whites would resist any effort to impose a black 
majority government and called for early elections to oust de klerk 
about 50000 whites including many women and children attended 
the rally under deep blue skies at the voortrekker monument a 
shrine to afrikaner nationalism organizers claimed 150000 people 
attended 
stay white and the struggle for a free state has begun 
said some of the posters carried by protesters 
the socalled new south africa of forced integration which 
the government is forcing on us gives us no other choice but to 
defend our rights treurnicht said as the huge throng cheered and 
clapped 
we shall not accept the threatened destruction of our nations 
freedom but will fight to restore that which has already been 
unjustly given away he said 
treurnicht denounced nelson mandela and his african national 
congress as communists and terrorists he claimed black 
nationalists would impose communist dictatorship if they gained 
power 
the anc hates the boer people and the white nation they 
demand our land they reject our right to exist he said as the 
crowd screamed its approval 
mandela addressed a rally in the nearby black township of 
atteridgeville where he told about 40000 cheering blacks that the 
right wing could not preserve white rule 
today at this moment in fact andries treurnicht that 
prophet of doom is meeting over that hill in order to oppose 
the effort made by the anc and the government to bring peace into 
this country mandela said we say to treurnicht we have 
defeated greater men than himself 
he will be defeated 
in cincinnati archbishop desmond tutu said if he had a chance 
to address the white demonstrators he would have told them that 
freedom will prevail 
id say to them you do have the right to hold that rally but 
ultimately it is selfdefeating he said what in fact are you 
seeking to do you are seeking to carve out for yourself a separate 
freedom 
the world has discovered that freedom is indivisible said 
tutu south africas anglican archbishop and nobel peace laureate 
treurnichts rally marked the launch of the right wings third 
freedom struggle a reference to two 19th century wars against 
britain treurnicht presented a freedom manifesto that called for 
nationwide struggle for a white state 
he denounced de klerk for moving to end whiteminority rule and 
share power with the black majority de klerk who came to power 
last august legalized the anc and released mandela in february 
after 27 years in prison but he has stopped short of supporting 
black majority rule 
treurnicht who received a thunderous ovation from the crowd as 
he arrived in a horsedrawn carriage was escorted by about 200 
horsemen in a commando or afrikaner war party 
the crowd waved hundreds of blue red white and green flags of 
the old transvaal republic which was defeated by britain in the 
boer war afrikaners whites of mainly dutch descent dominate 
south african politics 
scores of uniformed and armed members of ultraright groups 
attended the rally and some carried signs with slogans such as 
hang mandela 
of course im a racist the blacks are racist i know im 
better than blacks said one rightwinger who would not give his 
name 
in johannesburg de klerk predicted substantial changes in south 
africas relations with the rest of the world he returned saturday 
from 18 days of explaining his reform policies in europe 
i can report back to you today that substantial change in the 
relations of europe with south africa will come and i believe 
through europe the international community will follow he told 
about 1000 cheering supporters at jan smuts airport 
the government cannot be forced to call elections until 1994 and 
de klerk is confident he can carry out reforms and gain acceptance 
in that time 
treurnicht said little that was new and was vague on what the 
conservatives would do if the government refuses to hold elections 
he said his party would follow legal means of opposition 
as long as there is a constitutional path open whereby we can 
regain political control we will use that strategy to win a 
victory at the polling booth he said 
but treurnicht did make veiled references to a white backlash if 
de klerk ends white minority rule do not force our people to 
stand in your path and to challenge you to walk over us there 
is no boat waiting for us in the harbor he said 
the government contends the right wing cannot stop the reforms 
begun by de klerk but officials admit privately that many whites 
are flocking to the conservatives because of their opposition to 
ending white rule 
