a young former fugitive who confessed to 
three slayings was returned to delaware from louisiana on saturday 
and ordered held without bond in the slayings of his parents 1 
years ago 
charles cohen 25 had eluded capture until thursday when 
facing simple battery and attempted robbery charges under an 
assumed name he stunned spectators in a louisiana courtroom with 
his confession 
cohen disappeared at the same time the bodies of his parents 
martin and ethel were discovered on nov 14 1988 in their home 
in the northern delaware town of hockessin 
martin cohen 58 was director of the delaware state hospital 
the state psychiatric hospital his 63yearold wife was an 
occupational therapist 
cohen has told police the identity of the third person he claims 
to have killed attorney general charles oberly told a news 
conference saturday oberly would not release the identity of the 
person but said the homicide did not occur in delaware or a 
neighboring state 
the states top prosecutor said he expected police to confirm 
the details within 24 hours 
cohen managed to avoid capture despite publicity on the fox 
networks weekly television show americas most wanted he had 
long hair and facial hair when he disappeared but looked like an 
allamerican boy when he was captured new castle county police 
chief thomas gordon said 
cohen a former student at the university of delaware had been 
lead singer in a rock band in illinois 
police were still tracing cohens path as a fugitive but said 
he moved to new orleans in midfebruary from new york city 
at the time of his arrest cohen identified himself as james 
mcdowell said capt bob garner a sheriffs spokesman in gretna 
la 
cohen was closeted with new castle county police from his 
arrival in delaware around 1 pm until he was turned over for 
arraignment six hours later 
delaware magistrate paul smith ordered cohen held without bond 
on two firstdegree murder counts and cohen was taken to gander 
hill prison saturday night police said his preliminary hearing 
was set for june 5 
