<TEXT>
the first time raisa gorbachev met barbara 
bush the two were sharing a limousine during the rush of events 
that surrounded the 1987 washington summit between president reagan 
and raisas husband mikhail 
mrs gorbachev apparently had been briefed that the wife of the 
thenvice president was a whitehaired grandmotherly homemaker 
oh barbara i have to share with you a wonderful recipe for 
blueberry pie mrs gorbachev a doctor of philosophy told her 
hostess the best known dropout from the smith college class of 47 
the soviet visitor described a rudimentary recipe that sounded 
as if it came from a script barbara bush listened then asked 
skeptically raisa do you cook at home 
well yes sometimes i do replied mrs gorbachev 
well i never cook at home so lets talk about something 
else said mrs bush and the two women proceeded to converse in 
a more relaxed and less stilted fashion 
the anecdote which mrs bush herself enjoys telling makes two 
points 
raisa gorbachev ever the marxist lecturer tries to do her 
homework before she comes to a summit 
barbara bush is never at a loss for words and no one however 
high or mighty is immune from her wit 
the two first ladies will share the spotlight with their 
husbands thursday when bush welcomes gorbachev to the white house 
the wives will repair to the private residence for tea while their 
husbands talk in the oval office that evening the bushes will 
play host to the gorbachevs at a blacktie dinner 
friday the first ladies will fly to wellesley college in 
massachusetts where both will address the schools commencement 
that night the gorbachevs will be hosts for the bushes for dinner 
at the soviet embassy 
saturday the women probably will accompany their husbands to 
camp david the presidential retreat in the maryland mountains 75 
miles away sunday the gorbachevs will fly to minneapolis where 
she will visit with a middleclass family and then to california 
sharing the wellesley podium was mrs bushs idea she tendered 
the invitation long before 150 seniors signed a petition 
questioning her selection as commencement speaker 
the seniors challenged the wisdom of honoring a woman who has 
gained recognition through the achievements of her husband 
prominent feminists responded that they had no quarrel with the 
way mrs bush chose to lead her life mrs bush herself called it 
no big deal even i was 20 once 
barbara bush 64 is a publishers daughter from rye ny who 
dropped out of college in 1944 to marry her teenage sweetheart 
george a navy pilot and war hero she followed him to yale and 
then texas for a life in the oil fields 
apart from a wartime summer job in a bolt factory and a 
parttime stint at the yale coop mrs bush devoted herself to 
home and family raising five children a sixth daughter robin 
died of leukemia when she was 3 years old and holding the family 
together through 29 moves in her husbands peripatetic career in 
business politics and diplomacy 
a lifelong volunteer she adopted literacy as her personal cause 
when bush became vice president in 1981 since he was elected 
president 16 months ago she has spoken out on the plight of aids 
victims but has avoided delivering her views in public on abortion 
and other controversial issues 
her downtoearth ways her obvious love of family her 
fullsize figure and her white hair have all endeared her to 
americans across the political spectrum 
raisa gorbachev 58 is the siberianborn daughter of a railway 
worker she attended the soviet unions top academic institution 
moscow state university where she met her future husband a law 
student who lived in the same hostel 
while her husband rose through the party ranks she taught 
school and wrote a pioneering sociologylike dissertation on life 
in rural stavropols collective farms the gorbachevs are known to 
have a daughter who is a physician and are believed to also have 
a son 
when gorbachev became the communist partys agriculture 
secretary in 1978 she joined the philosophy faculty at moscow 
state she stepped down when her husband became the partys general 
secretary in 1985 
strongwilled and stylish the british press once dubbed her 
soviet realisms answer to princess diana she has been in the 
public eye far more than the wives of past soviet leaders while 
the coverage of her foreign trips has been far less extensive at 
home than abroad her penchant for finer living has aroused some 
enmity one of her husbands bestknown opponents maverick boris 
yeltsin even criticized her in a 1987 speech to party leaders 
soon thereafter yeltsin was stripped of his party office 
however mrs bush and mrs gorbachev get along their relations 
will likely be better than those between nancy reagan and the 
soviet first lady 
the nancyraisa feud was played out in soap opera fashion at 
summits whenever they met and once when they didnt mrs 
gorbachev showed up unexpectedly in reykjavik iceland for the 
hurriedly called 1986 summit while mrs reagan who had been told 
her counterpart would not come stayed home 
on her 1987 visit to washington mrs gorbachev kept the reagan 
white house guessing about her schedule mrs reagan had trouble 
pinning her down for a white house tour and when she did come she 
described the presidential mansion as more of a museum of 
american history than a regular house 
in moscow during the june 1988 summit mrs reagan described her 
testy relationship with mrs gorbachev as a mexican standoff 
in her 1989 memoirs my turn mrs reagan wrote my 
fundamental impression of raisa gorbachev was that she never 
stopped talking or lecturing to be more accurate 
as part of the gorbachevs tour of the united states he is said 
to be trying to set up a breakfast meeting with reagan in san 
francisco whether mrs reagan and mrs gorbachev would join their 
husbands isnt known 
