in terms of prices 
with things going so well the industry is wary of anything that 
could reverse the trend 
from the producers standpoint deterioration of the market is 
the no 1 fear wehler says 
two primary concerns are food safety and animal rights not only 
are consumers asking more and more questions about the chemicals in 
their food but they also are organizing boycotts 
memories of last years alar uproar that hurt apple sales and 
halted use of the chemical are fresh in the minds of farmers the 
pork industry has its own memories of the nitrite scare that 
plagued bacon sales a decade ago 
weve all seen what can happen with demand for a product 
wehler says 
in an attempt to avoid becoming a target again the pork council 
has organized a quality assurance program to encourage farmers to 
adopt safe practices in the use of livestock medication and to 
highlight the dangers posed by tainted feed 
the animal rights movement also is on the mind of livestock 
